      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@AbhayNagaraj It doesn&#39;t matter if you try to establish a connection to a closed port on an existing server or to a port on a non-exiting/non-reachable server. In both cases you get an <code>java.net.ConnectException</code>. The only difference is the message and the time it takes until you get the exception. If the server exists and just the port is wrong you usually have no delay. In case of the non-existent server you will get a time-out after the configured time."
